meness which gave me so piercing a thrill. He on his part saw in me a doubtful imitator. I wish to lay stress, however, on the dimness of those ideas of his. He would certainly not have understood my comments upon them, the dullard.

“I am afraid there is not much I can do for you at the moment,” I answered coldly. “But leave me your address.”

I took out my notebook and silver pencil.

